<F P=106> ["Exclusive" report by Nitzan Horowitz] </F>
  [Excerpt] Madrid -- Israel has decided to establish full 
diplomatic relations with Andorra, a tiny country wedged between 
Spain and France in the Pyrenees. 
  The Foreign Ministry decided to appoint Dr. Ya'aqov Kohen, 
Israel's ambassador in Madrid, as a nonresident ambassador in 
Andorra. He will present his credentials to the Andorran 
leaders at the end of this month. [passage omitted] 

